The paper deals with a wire-tap channel inspired by compressed sensing, which involves the use of linear projections to estimate sparse vectors. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Information Theory and Probability (cs.ITP) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the secrecy capacity of the channel, which relates to the security of the communication, and hence, the paper may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of compressed sensing matrices and the study of the large system limit suggest that the paper may also belong to the Mathematical Methods (cs.MM) or Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories.
